    "created_at": "2017-05-12T13:01:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-05-12T13:01:37Z",
    "body": "I think that returning a promise is a cleaner solution that will be also more obvious to new developers.\r\nIf that's not possible (for example, because of backwards compatibility), i would vote for a callback, because having a consistent API within a project in my opinion is more important than doing it \"right\"."
